<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 6:22PM EST  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT PARTS OF PERRY...FRANKLIN...AND
CUMBERLAND COUNTIES...
HAZARDS...An area of heavy snow accompanied by winds of up to 30 MPH
which can rapidly reduce visibility to less than one mile.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 622 PM EST, an area of heavy snow was near
Shippensburg moving east at 25 MPH.
THIS AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Newville around 635 PM EST.
This includes the following Interstates...
The Pennsylvania Turnpike from mile markers 196 to 217.
Interstate 81 from mile markers 29 to 38.
SAFETY INFO...
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this area of
heavy snow. Rapid changes in visibility and potentially slick roads
may lead to accidents.
&amp;&amp;</description>
